# Operating System

The Jack Operating System is a set of standard library classes written in Jack that provide essential services: math, memory management, string handling, and I/O. This is the final layer of the Nand to Tetris software stack.

## OS Modules

The Jack OS consists of 8 modules:

| Class     | Purpose                                          |
|-----------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Math      | Multiplication, division, square root            |
| String    | String creation, concatenation, comparison       |
| Array     | Array allocation and deallocation                |
| Output    | Character and string output to screen            |
| Screen    | Pixel, line, rectangle, circle drawing           |
| Keyboard  | Reading key presses and characters               |
| Memory    | Heap management (alloc/dealloc)                  |
| Sys       | System startup, error handling, timer            |

## Memory Management

The Memory class implements heap management using a **free list** algorithm:

```jack
class Memory {
    static Array freeList;

    function void init() {
        let freeList = 2048;  // heap starts after OS code
        let freeList[0] = 0;  // next = null (end of list)
        let freeList[1] = 14336 - 2048;  // size of free block
        return;
    }

    function int alloc(int size) {
        // Find a free block, split if needed
        // Returns address of allocated block
    }

    function void deAlloc(int address) {
        // Return block to free list
    }
}
```

