## Screen Graphics

The Screen class provides pixel-level drawing. The screen is 512 x 256 pixels, memory-mapped at address 16384 (SCREEN). Each row is 32 words (512 bits).

```jack
class Screen {
    function void drawPixel(int x, int y) {
        // Compute word address and bit mask
        // Write to screen memory map
    }

    function void drawLine(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2) {
        // Bresenham's line algorithm
    }

    function void drawRectangle(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2) {
        // Loop drawing horizontal lines
    }

    function void drawCircle(int cx, int cy, int r) {
        // Midpoint circle algorithm
    }
}
```

## System Bootstrap

The Sys class initializes the OS:

```jack
class Sys {
    function void init() {
        // Initialize all OS classes
        do Math.init();
        do Output.init();
        do Screen.init();
        do Keyboard.init();
        do Memory.init();
        // Start the user's program
        do Main.main();
        // Halt
        do Sys.halt();
    }
}
```

